I also doubled the garlic and red pepper and used 1/2 the olive oil. I think the amount of olive oil depends on how much eggplants you have - you should have everything coated without being overly greasy. I roasted my batch for an extra 8 minutes - I thought this added to the caramelization and really released the sugars of all the vegetables. In the end, I served this on bagel chips with just a drop of aged balsamic for the perfect bite.

