Rating: 4
This dish was fantastic!! Instead of it being an appetizer I turned it into a main like another reviewer suggested. For me I doubled the garlic, added half an onion, tripled the red pepper flakes, added some oregano, and 3/4 cup olive oil. Roasted everything together then pureed it. Separately I browned some ground turkey then combined the meat and sauce in a pan to simmer. The sauce was to thick for pasta so I added some low sodium V8 juice and a bit of balsamic. Put over pasta with some romano cheese and it was delicious!!!!!! I love recipes that you can easily take them and turn them into something else, this one is a great foundation for so many yummy dishes.

