Rating: 3
Took the suggestion from the intro to serve it on bread. crackers or whatever. Here's what I did: Added sweet yellow onion, chopped in a crescent shape. Used TJ jarred roasted pepper to save time (thanks for the suggestion). Also, as someone suggested, I only used enough oil to coat everything as I stirred it up before roasting. It was NOT a cup of oil, that's for sure. Roasted for 20 minutes. Got TJ's pizza dough and prepared it for the roasted veggies. Sprinkled the dough with a thin layer of finely grated parm. then the roasted veggies. Added a light layer of shredded fontina/parm. (Don't over cheese!) Baked at 400 for 15 minutes, then broiled until top was golden brown. Served it up. Fresh, fresh flavor. Drag. Nothing left for lunch tomorrow.

